Description:
This SQL script contains a collection of basic analytical queries used to explore
Premier League match data. Its purpose is to transform raw football records into
clear summary metrics related to dataset size, scoring, match outcomes, and match
discipline.

The script relies on core SQL functions and operators such as COUNT(), SUM(),
AVG(), MAX(), ROUND(), and DISTINCT to calculate totals, averages, and extreme
values. It also uses UNION ALL to combine multiple summary results into a single
output, CASE WHEN to classify match outcomes, and GROUP BY / ORDER BY to organize
aggregated results. Simple arithmetic operations are applied to combine related
columns, such as home and away goals or cards.

These functions are used because they provide an efficient and readable way to
summarize football data, identify patterns, and answer practical analytical
questions using straightforward SQL logic.